						<summary>

						<p>This may also be a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttāma-Chōḷa.</hi> It states that <hi rend="bold">Śrī Gōvindapāḍi Mārāyaṇaṉ of Uruppuṭṭūr</hi> a member of the <hi rend="italic">ālum-gaṇam</hi> of Avaninārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam consecrated an image of god <hi rend="bold">Maṇavāḷapperumāḷ</hi> (in the temple) and made provision for the mid-day offering to the deity by an endowment of land left in charge of the servants of the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> attached to the temple. </p>						

						</summary>
